  <prompt>
Close UAT issue 6 from the 2026-06-18 widget-parity audit. Hoist the `useKanbanColumns` hook from the SmartTodo Code Page into the `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` peer package; render the widget items as Today / Tomorrow / Future grouped sections (NOT a full drag-drop Kanban — just date-bucket headers + flat lists per group). Code Page consumes the hoisted hook from the peer package; no duplication.
  </prompt>

  <role>
React engineer comfortable with peer-package hoists (the `@spaarke/ui-components` → `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` style), Fluent v9 styling, and the threshold-based date-bucket logic in `useKanbanColumns`.
  </role>

  <goal>
Widget renders 3 grouped sections — "Today", "Tomorrow", "Future" — with items bucketed via the same `useKanbanColumns` logic the Code Page uses. The hook lives in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` (peer package); the Code Page's local copy is deleted and the import points to the peer package. Empty buckets are visible (with a sensible "No items" state) so users can see the grouping structure even before scrolling. The widget's selection model (from R4-099) carries over — selecting an item in any bucket enables the Open action.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="audit-findings">projects/smart-todo-r4/notes/d-widget-parity-audit-2026-06-18.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/smart-todo-r4/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="hook-source">src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/hooks/useKanbanColumns.ts</file>
    <file purpose="threshold-prefs-reference">src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/hooks/useUserPreferences.ts</file>
    <file purpose="peer-package-barrel">src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/index.ts</file>
    <file purpose="widget">src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/widgets/SmartTodoWidget/SmartTodoWidget.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="pattern">.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 + Griffel `makeStyles` + semantic tokens mandatory; no v8 components, no inline styles</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared hook MUST live in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` peer package — NOT in `src/solutions/SmartTodo/` after hoist</constraint>
    <constraint source="No regression">Code Page's existing Kanban rendering MUST continue to work after the hoist; the consumer change is a single import-source swap</constraint>
    <constraint source="Widget scope">Widget renders GROUPED LISTS, NOT a full drag-drop Kanban. Drag-drop is Code Page only; do NOT hoist react-dnd or the column-drop logic.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-09">Rebuild + redeploy from master after R4-099 + R4-100 + R4-101 all land; this task is one of three; do NOT deploy from branch</constraint>
    <constraint source="durable user instruction">spaarkedev1 deploys are master-only; do NOT propose a branch deploy</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>peer-package hoist + Kanban column bucketing</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENTIZATION-AUDIT.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/hooks/useKanbanColumns.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/hooks/useUserPreferences.ts</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-v9-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-component-library.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Peer-package hoist precedent" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components (created in R4-020)">
        The peer package was created in R4-020 to host the widget. Hoisting `useKanbanColumns` into it extends that pattern. Mirror the existing widget's barrel export pattern.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Code Page consumer pattern" location="src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/SmartToDo.tsx">
        Code Page's Kanban consumer uses `useKanbanColumns(items, userPrefs)`. After hoist, the import source changes from `../hooks/useKanbanColumns` to `@spaarke/smart-todo-components`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT screenshot 2026-06-18 showed the widget rendering a flat list of items with no Today/Tomorrow/Future grouping — but the user expects the same date-bucket organization the Code Page's Kanban provides. The hoist was explicitly deferred from R4-020 (called out as "13-file rich-feature subtree" in the R4-020 closeout). This task is that hoist, scoped to JUST `useKanbanColumns` + grouped list rendering (no drag-drop, no full Kanban).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="R4-020" status="must-complete">Peer package exists</dependency>
      <dependency task="R4-030" status="must-complete">Code Page Kanban + useKanbanColumns are the source of truth being hoisted</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R4-099 (W-1) is parallel-safe with this task — different files (LW shim + widget chrome vs peer package + widget rendering). Selection state added by R4-099 should remain compatible with grouped rendering.</item>
      <item>R4-100 (W-2) is parallel-safe with this task — different files (Code Page launch context + shim callbacks vs peer package hook + widget rendering).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check">Confirm context &lt; 70%. Read the audit-findings note.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Read source hook">Read `src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/hooks/useKanbanColumns.ts` end-to-end. Note: signature, dependencies (any imports from `src/solutions/SmartTodo`?), threshold prefs shape, date-bucket logic.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Identify hoist transitives">Inventory what useKanbanColumns depends on — types (ITodo, KanbanColumn), constants (threshold defaults), utilities (date comparisons). Anything currently in `src/solutions/SmartTodo` that the peer package would need must also move OR be re-exported from the peer package.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Hoist the hook">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/hooks/useKanbanColumns.ts` with the same logic. Move (do NOT duplicate) any pure transitive dependencies that the Code Page does not need to retain locally. Add to peer package barrel (`src/index.ts`).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update Code Page consumer">In the Code Page (likely `src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/SmartToDo.tsx` and any other consumer), change the import source from `../hooks/useKanbanColumns` to `@spaarke/smart-todo-components`. Delete the local `useKanbanColumns.ts` file. Verify Code Page builds + Kanban renders unchanged.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Widget grouped rendering">In `SmartTodoWidget.tsx`, call `useKanbanColumns(items, prefs)` (where prefs = sensible widget defaults or pulled from `useUserPreferences` if cheap). Replace the flat `renderItem` loop with 3 grouped sections — each section has a header (column label + count) and a list of items. Empty groups render a "No items" placeholder. Selection model from R4-099 continues to work across groups.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Styles">Update `SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts` with grouped-section styles — section header (subtle background, smaller font), section list (existing card styles), section gap (Fluent v9 spacing tokens).</step>
    <step order="7" name="Build">`npm run build` (tsc) in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components` + `npm run build` (Vite) in `src/solutions/SmartTodo` + `npm run build` (Vite) in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace`. All three must pass clean.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Quality gates">Run `code-review` + `adr-check` on modified files per task-execute Step 9.5. ADR-012 is the binding one (shared-lib hoist rule).</step>
    <step order="9" name="Update task status">Flip POML status to `complete`. Update TASK-INDEX.md row + header counts. Note the closeout of the "13-file rich-feature subtree" follow-up from R4-020 (this task scope is just the grouping hook; full Kanban hoist remains a future task if ever needed).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build (tsc on peer package; Vite on SmartTodo + LegalWorkspace)</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit (main session pushes)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">New: src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/hooks/useKanbanColumns.ts (hoisted hook)</output>
    <output type="code">Modified: src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components/src/index.ts (barrel export)</output>
